"The Office has not discovered any signs of anti-competitive proceedings in this case, so there is no reason to intervene in any way.
None of the service providers have a leading position, i.e. they have no relatively greater responsibility for their market facts.
The tools needed to open up the mobile market for virtual service providers are also likely to be lacking in the telecommunications regulator,” said Chalupa.
Presenting the market leader position is one of many points of debate.
There is, of course, an analysis of the relevant markets developed by <0xC4><0x8C>T<0xC3><0x9A>, on the basis of which telecommunications is the single market from the point of view of competition.
Of course, there is not a single Czech service provider in a leading position on such a market.
However, some legal experts also offer a different perspective - the creation of a virtual service provider always requires the approval of the network operator.
And the mobile service provider - relatively logically - has a monopoly on its own network.
So it is necessarily dominant in a certain segment.
But even if we did not accept this argument, <0xC3><0x9A>OHS should have a minimum incentive for three mobile service providers to act in a similar manner.
In the meantime, complaints from a number of interested parties (including the already mentioned GTS Novara company) show that they encounter very similar obstacles in the course of negotiations with all service providers.
